Program: Crossing Continents
Title: Starting from Scratch in Uganda
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b0939wgq
Last Broadcast Date: Mon 18 Sep 2017
Uganda has now taken in more than a million refugees who have fled civil war in neighbouring South Sudan. And more are coming every day. It's said that Uganda has the most generous refugee policy in the world, with new arrivals given land and allowed to work. But the majority of South Sudanese refugees are women and children who have lost almost everything and, as Ruth Alexander discovers, the reality of starting a new life from scratch is far from straightforward. Produced by John Murphy. Show less